"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1052262","Treasury","false","2019-02-07","<p>HM Treasury does not centrally hold information on historical capital spending per constituency. However, HM Treasury does publish regional breakdowns of capital spending by economic category in <em>Public Expenditure Statistical Analyses 2018</em>. For example, on p.138 (attached) is a breakdown of capital spending on transport per region, including capital spending in the South East.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2019-02-07T09:30:47.713Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1052262/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1052262/answer","PQWhmt_PQW_17-19_2019_01499 - vUpload2.pdf","PQWhmt_PQW_17-19_2019_01499 - vUpload2.pdf","pq attachment","pq attachment","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1052262/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2019-01-31","Capital Investment: Dover","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the capital account spending has been in Dover constituency in each year between 2009 and 2018.","false","Biography information for Charlie Elphicke","Dover","Charlie Elphicke","215146"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1052263","Treasury","false","2019-02-06","<p>This information is not held centrally. HM Treasury do not collect expenditure information at a constituency level. The Ministry of Housing and Local Government produce local government expenditure statistics but this doesn’t align with constituency boundaries.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2019-02-06T15:50:59.06Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1052263/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1052263/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1052263/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2019-01-31","Public Expenditure: Dover","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the total government spending per person in the Dover constituency has been in each year between 2009 and 2018.","false","Biography information for Charlie Elphicke","Dover","Charlie Elphicke","215147"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1052264","Department for Transport","false","2019-02-11","<p>Transport capital funding from Government is allocated to local authorities at upper tier level, in this case Kent County Council (KCC). The Department does not hold figures for the Dover Constituency. The total capital expenditure on highways and transport (from all funding sources) as reported by KCC can be found in the table below.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Kent</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2008/09</p></td><td><p>£73,783K</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2009/10</p></td><td><p>£86,001K</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010/11</p></td><td><p>£89,584K</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011/12</p></td><td><p>£54,839K</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012/13</p></td><td><p>£48,450K</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013/14</p></td><td><p>£112,115K</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014/15</p></td><td><p>£60,303K</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015/16</p></td><td><p>£54,665K</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016/17</p></td><td><p>£77,794K</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2017/18</p></td><td><p>£63,556K</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><strong><strong><strong><strong><strong><strong> </strong></strong></strong></strong></strong></strong></p><p> </p><p>We have also provided Kent County Council with significant extra funding to assist with the preparations for if the UK leaves the EU without a deal. This is part of the Operation Brock contingency planning.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2019-02-11T10:12:20.463Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1052264/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1052264/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1052264/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-01-31","Transport: Dover","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the transport infrastructure capital account spending has been in Dover constituency in each year between 2009 and 2018.","false","Biography information for Charlie Elphicke","Dover","Charlie Elphicke","215148"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1052265","Cabinet Office","false","2019-02-05","<p>Further to my answer of 18 January 2018, (https://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2018-01-08/121510/) the Royal Mint will produce a coin to commemorate the UK leaving the European Union.</p><p>The Royal Mint has a long-established tradition of producing coins in order to commemorate historic moments, including the 2012 Olympics, the UK’s accession to the European Economic Community, and the centenary of the First World War.</p><p> </p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2019-02-05T19:04:57.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1052265/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1052265/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1052265/answer",,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2019-01-31","Brexit: Festivals and Special Occasions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, further to the Answer of 18 January 2018 to Question 121510, whether the Government has plans for ceremonial or official events to mark the formal exit of the UK from the European Union.","false","Biography information for Patrick Grady","Glasgow North","Patrick Grady","215222"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1052266","Prime Minister","false","2019-02-05","<p>A list was previously published in September 2018. We will publish an updated list, routinely in due course.</p>","Maidenhead","Mrs Theresa May",,"2019-02-05T15:22:54.01Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1052266/answer","Biography information for Mrs Theresa May","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1052266/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1052266/answer",,,,,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2019-01-31","Parliamentary Private Secretaries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, if she will publish a list of hon. Members appointed as Parliamentary Private Secretaries to (a) Government Departments, (b) Ministers and (c) Secretaries of State.","false","Biography information for Patrick Grady","Glasgow North","Patrick Grady","215223"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1052267","Treasury","false","2019-02-07","<p>There are no plans to review the funding allocation made to the Equitable Life Payment Scheme. Since 2010, we have taken more action than any previous government to resolve this issue by allocating up to £1.5bn, tax free, for payment to affected policyholders.</p>","Salisbury","John Glen",,"2019-02-07T15:32:10.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1052267/answer","Biography information for John Glen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1052267/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1052267/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2019-01-31","Equitable Life Assurance Society: Compensation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether he has plans to conduct a second review of the value of the Equitable Life contingency fund.","false","Biography information for Andrea Jenkyns","Morley and Outwood","Andrea Jenkyns","215253"
