"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1052277","Cabinet Office","false","2019-02-06","<p>The unaudited total reported spend through the Spend Analytic Database for consultancy services in the last five full financial years across all Government departments including ALB’s is as follows:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>£648 million</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>£676 million</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>£635 million</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016-17</p></td><td><p>£964 million</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2017-18</p></td><td><p>£1,549 million</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"2019-02-06T17:13:30.35Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1052277/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1052277/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1052277/answer",,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2019-01-31","Government Departments: Consultants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how much money was spent from the public purse on consultancy fees as recorded by the Cabinet Office Spend Analytic Database by each Department, in each of the last five financial years,","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","215097"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1052278","Home Office","false","2019-02-06","<p>The UK Government committed €50 million in order to implement a range of agreed actions under the terms of the 2018 Sandhurst Treaty. Payments from this package have been made across the course of the 18/19 financial year as and when required by specific projects. The agreed programme of work is designed to improve security at the shared border in Northern France, reduce illegal migration flows towards northern French ports and support France in returning migrants with no legal right to be in Europe. We are forecasting to spend the full package allocated to this work.</p><p>Within this package, £3.6 million was specifically allocated to funding the development of the Dublin process to support transfers of eligible children to the UK. The Dublin III Regulation is a long-standing mechanism between EU Member States to determine responsibility for examining asylum claims. The Government has committed to publishing regular updates on the number of requests processed under the Dublin III Regulation. The latest figures will be published on 28th February 2019 as part of the wider quarterly release of Migration Statistics.</p><p>Migration cooperation between the UK and France, including implementation of the Sandhurst Treaty is overseen by the senior official UK-France Migration Committee, which generally meets alternately in Paris and London on a bi-monthly basis. The minutes of those meetings are confidential and to disclose them would risk injuring relations with an important foreign ally.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","215156 ; 215157 ; 215158","2019-02-06T17:02:17.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1052278/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1052278/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1052278/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-01-31","Undocumented Migrants: France","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how much money has been paid from the public purse to authorities in France in relation to the Sandhurst Treaty 2018; and on what dates those payments were made.","false","Biography information for Charlie Elphicke","Dover","Charlie Elphicke","215155"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1052279","Cabinet Office","false","2019-02-05","<p>The Management Consultancy Framework (MCF) agreements have been designed by the Crown Commercial Service (CCS) to support the increased use of SMEs and a large proportion of framework suppliers are SMEs.</p><p> </p><p>Since 1st April 2014, 10.05% of total spend through the following CCS managed commercial arrangements has gone to SMEs:</p><p> </p><p>ConsultancyONE (RM1502)</p><p>MCF (RM3745)</p><p>MCF2 (RM6008)</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"2019-02-05T17:58:25.007Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1052279/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1052279/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1052279/answer",,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2019-01-31","Crown Commercial Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what proportion of consultancy agreement business tendered through Crown Commercial Service Consultancy agreements went to SMEs in each of the last five financial years.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","215098"
