"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051473","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-02-04","<p>On 30 January, the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care announced that the Pre-exposure Prophylaxis (PrEP) Impact trial would be expanded to 26,000 people. Work is underway with partners to take this forward. The PrEP Oversight Board has requested information on local capacity to make the additional places available, and will review this later in February. The Secretary of State also announced the Government’s commitment to ending new HIV transmissions in England by 2030. To support this work, an expert group will be established to develop an action plan over the course of this year. The important role of PrEP, as part of combination HIV prevention efforts, will be considered as part of this process.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","214542 ; 214543","2019-02-04T18:09:57.12Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051473/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051473/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051473/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-01-30","HIV Infection: Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what assessment he has made of the effect of the delay to the proposed doubling of places on the PrEP Impact Trial on his Department's commitment to ending new HIV transmissions by 2030.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","214541"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051474","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-02-04","<p>On 30 January, the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care announced that the Pre-exposure Prophylaxis (PrEP) Impact trial would be expanded to 26,000 people. Work is underway with partners to take this forward. The PrEP Oversight Board has requested information on local capacity to make the additional places available, and will review this later in February. The Secretary of State also announced the Government’s commitment to ending new HIV transmissions in England by 2030. To support this work, an expert group will be established to develop an action plan over the course of this year. The important role of PrEP, as part of combination HIV prevention efforts, will be considered as part of this process.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","214541 ; 214543","2019-02-04T18:09:57.183Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051474/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051474/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051474/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-01-30","HIV Infection: Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, when he plans to introduce the doubling of places on the PrEP Impact Trial.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","214542"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051475","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-02-04","<p>On 30 January, the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care announced that the Pre-exposure Prophylaxis (PrEP) Impact trial would be expanded to 26,000 people. Work is underway with partners to take this forward. The PrEP Oversight Board has requested information on local capacity to make the additional places available, and will review this later in February. The Secretary of State also announced the Government’s commitment to ending new HIV transmissions in England by 2030. To support this work, an expert group will be established to develop an action plan over the course of this year. The important role of PrEP, as part of combination HIV prevention efforts, will be considered as part of this process.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","214541 ; 214542","2019-02-04T18:09:57.213Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051475/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051475/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051475/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-01-30","HIV Infection: Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, by what date the proposed doubling of places on its PrEP Impact Trial will be achieved.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","214543"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051476","Cabinet Office","false","2019-02-04","<p>Multiple officials from the Government Commercial Function, including the Crown Representative and other officials from the Markets and Suppliers team, interact with a range of Interserve employees through formal meetings, conference calls, individual phone calls, and other forums (including meetings hosted by other departments), as they do with most Strategic Suppliers. There will normally be multiple such interactions per week. Ministers in the Cabinet Office receive a weekly update on supplier issues including Strategic Suppliers.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"2019-02-04T16:10:07.97Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051476/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051476/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051476/answer",,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2019-01-30","Interserve","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, pursuant to the Answer of 20 December 2019 to Question 204484 on Interserve and the Answer of 24 January 2019 to Question 204485, for what reason the information provided does not include the number of meetings held by (a) Ministers in his Department and (b) Cabinet Office Markets and Suppliers team with representatives of Interserve plc in 2018.","false","Biography information for Rachel Reeves","Leeds West","Rachel Reeves","214537"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051477","Northern Ireland Office","false","2019-02-04","<p>I am in regular contact with the leaders of the Northern Ireland parties and I remain focused on bringing the parties together to work towards re-establishing devolved government in Northern Ireland.</p><p> </p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2019-02-04T13:00:02.207Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051477/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051477/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051477/answer",,,,,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2019-01-30","Political Parties: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, when she last chaired round table talks between the leaders of the main political parties in Northern Ireland.","false","Biography information for Lady Hermon","North Down","Lady Hermon","214519"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051478","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-02-07","<p>The NHS Business Services Authority does not hold data for FreeStyle Libre flash glucose monitoring devices. However, prescription data for FreeStyle Libre Sensors prescribed in clinical commissioning groups in the financial years 2017/18 and 2018/19 to date can be found in the attached table.</p><p> </p><p>This data refers to FreeStyle Libre Sensor packs that include one sensor, one sensor applicator, and one wipe.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2019-02-07T13:55:36.203Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051478/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051478/answer","PQ214470 Data Completed.xlsx","PQ214470 Data Completed.xlsx","PQ214470 attached data","PQ214470 attached data","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051478/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-01-30","Diabetes: Medical Equipment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many Abbott FreeStyle Libre flash glucose monitoring devices and sensors local clinical commissioning groups prescribed in (a) 2017-18 (b) 2018-19 to date.","true","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","214470"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051479","Department for Transport","false","2019-02-04","<p>There are already charges that exist for certain drone users, when applying to the CAA for permission to operate commercially or for an exemption from an Air Navigation Order article. When registration of drone operators is implemented later this year, drone operators will be required to pay the CAA a registration charge in order to fund the running and maintenance of the service. The CAA will consult on the structure of the proposed charging later this year.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2019-02-04T15:12:42.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051479/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051479/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051479/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-01-30","Unmanned Air Vehicles: Regulation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what plans he has to recoup the cost of regulating drones from their users or manufacturers.","false","Biography information for Sir Greg Knight","East Yorkshire","Sir Greg Knight","214515"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051480","Northern Ireland Office","false","2019-02-04","<p>I have made clear that I am ready to consider all proposals which could support the parties in finding an agreement to restore the Executive. As always, all options remain on the table.</p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2019-02-04T13:01:10.197Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051480/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051480/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051480/answer",,,,,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2019-01-30","Political Parties: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what plans she has to appoint an independent mediator to chair discussions with the main political parties in Northern Ireland to restore devolution.","false","Biography information for Lady Hermon","North Down","Lady Hermon","214520"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051481","Northern Ireland Office","false","2019-02-04","<p>A second reduction to MLA salaries took effect last month, bringing the total reduction to 27.5%. While the Assembly is not sitting, I recognise that MLAs continue to be active in constituency work. The reduction that has been implemented reflects the work MLAs have been doing in the current period and is in line with the recommendations of former Assembly clerk and chief executive Trevor Reaney.</p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2019-02-04T09:55:07.667Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051481/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051481/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051481/answer",,,,,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2019-01-30","Northern Ireland Assembly: Members","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, when she plans to further reduce the salaries of Members of the Legislative Assembly in the continued absence of a functioning Northern Ireland Assembly.","false","Biography information for Lady Hermon","North Down","Lady Hermon","214521"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051482","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-02-07","<p>The information requested is not centrally held.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2019-02-07T13:44:20.913Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051482/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051482/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051482/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-01-30","Diabetes: Medical Equipment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what the average length of time taken is for the FreeStyle Libre sensors to be issued to people with diabetes through the NHS.","true","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","214471"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051483","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-02-08","<p>The cost of 1 FreeStyle Libre sensor, 1 sensor applicator, and 1 wipe is £35 as listed in the February 2019 Drug Tariff.</p><p> </p><p>Net Ingredient Cost is the basic price of a drug as stated in Part II Clause 8 of the Drug Tariff.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2019-02-08T12:32:42.28Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051483/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051483/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051483/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-01-30","Diabetes: Medical Equipment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what is the cost to the NHS is of each FreeStyle Libre flash glucose monitoring device.","true","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","214472"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051484","Department for Transport","false","2019-02-04","<p>Many drone manufacturers already voluntarily implement geo-fencing around sensitive infrastructure such as airports and prisons in the UK. The UK has been participating in negotiations in the EU to mandate geo-fencing as a product standard for all drones. The Department for Transport will continue to work with manufacturers to implement geo-fencing in their products.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2019-02-04T14:29:57.6Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051484/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051484/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051484/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-01-30","Unmanned Air Vehicles: Regulation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the technical feasibility of requiring drones to be fitted with geofencing software which prevents their operation around certain sites including airports, high-population density areas and national security sites.","false","Biography information for Sir Greg Knight","East Yorkshire","Sir Greg Knight","214516"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051485","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-02-07","<p>On 14 November 2018, it was announced that flash glucose monitors will be available on prescription for every patient who qualifies for them, in line with National Health Service clinical guidelines.</p><p> </p><p>The Department has not made any representations to Abbott since.</p><p> </p><p>Clinical commissioning groups (CCGs) are responsible for commissioning diabetes services. In doing so, CCGs need to ensure that the services they provide are fit for purpose, reflect the needs of the local population, are based on the available evidence, and take into account national guidelines. This should include consideration of access to diabetes technologies such as FreeStyle Libre.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2019-02-07T15:18:43.047Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051485/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051485/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051485/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-01-30","Diabetes: Medical Equipment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what representations his Department has made to the pharmaceutical company Abbott on the availability of FreeStyle Libre being issued to people with Type 1 diabetes from April 2019.","true","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","214473"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051486","Department for Education","false","2019-02-04","<p>I refer the hon. Member for South Shields to the answer I gave on 18 January 2018 to Question <a href="https://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;uin=122517" target="_blank">122517</a> where six local authorities named in were issued non-time-limited directions in January 2015.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2019-02-04T16:32:46.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051486/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051486/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051486/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2019-01-30","Children: Social Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 18 January 2018 to Question 122517 on children: social services, whether the six local authorities named in that answer are still exempt from statutory guidance.","false","Biography information for Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","South Shields","Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","214567"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051487","Treasury","false","2019-02-07","<p>UK-based lenders are subject to extensive prudential disclosure requirements under UK law, including for loans made to Governments. The Capital Requirements Regulation requires firms to disclose the geographic distribution of their credit exposures, including those to central banks and governments. These are only required to be disclosed if the loans are material, in accordance with European Banking Authority guidelines. Similarly, the geographical distribution will be broken down to show the areas for which there are material exposures. Lending to a specific country may not be disclosed specifically as lending to that country’s government if it makes up a relatively small amount of the firm’s activity. Instead, the lending would be grouped together with other small exposures to foreign governments under ‘other’ categories.</p><p> </p><p>It is firms’ responsibility to ensure adequate assurance over their disclosures and they are required to have policies for assessing the appropriateness of their disclosures, including their verification and frequency.</p><p> </p><p>Firms’ compliance with disclosure guidelines will generally be subject to review from their Internal Audit function. As the relevant competent authority, the Prudential Regulation Authority (PRA) takes a risk-based approach to supervision, which will affect whether each individual firm’s disclosures are subject to a compliance review.</p>","Salisbury","John Glen","214661 ; 214662","2019-02-07T15:43:14.847Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051487/answer","Biography information for John Glen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051487/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1051487/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2019-01-30","Overseas Loans: Mozambique","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the Answer of 28th January to Question 210062 on Loans: Mozambique, what information UK-based lenders to foreign governments have to disclose and to whom under UK prudential disclosure requirements.","false","Biography information for Dan Carden","Liverpool, Walton","Dan Carden","214660"
